Infer file type

Source: R/file_types.R
px_file_types.Rd

The px_file_types() function inferres mass spectrometry and proteomics file types based on a currated table of file types and associated patterns. This table can be accessed with file_types(). See the examples below for the content of the tables.

The file types table is generated by scripts/make_file_types.R.

file_types()

px_file_types(fls, types = file_types())

Arguments

fls

character() of file names whose types need to be inferred based on their file extenstion.

types

data.frame of file types. Default is file_types().

Value

A data.frame with the filenames and their inferred types.

Author

Laurent Gatto with contributions from Dr. Samuel Wein to identify several file types.

px_file_types("foo")
#>   file type
#> 1  foo <NA>
px_file_types("foo.mzML")
#>       file type
#> 1 foo.mzML  raw
px_file_types("foo.raw")
#>      file   type
#> 1 foo.raw binary
px_file_types("foo.txt")
#>      file type
#> 1 foo.txt  doc
px_file_types("foo.R")
#>    file type
#> 1 foo.R code
px_file_types("foo.fasta")
#>        file type
#> 1 foo.fasta  fas

px_file_types(c("foo", "foo.mzML", "foo.R", "foo.fasta"))
#>        file type
#> 1       foo <NA>
#> 2  foo.mzML  raw
#> 3     foo.R code
#> 4 foo.fasta  fas
